properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from High Island to Freeport TX out 20 NM
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 5 at 6:57AM CST until February 5 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX
properties.description:
...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING
TO 4 AM CST THURSDAY...

* WHAT...A Dense Fog Advisory is in effect. Dense fog will
reduce visibility to one quarter mile or less.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from High Island to Freeport TX out 20
NM.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 8 AM CST this
morning. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 6 PM this evening
to 4 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST THIS MORNING
